QA Test Plan                                                                                                                               
 ## Test Plan Overview

The Test Plan defines the overall testing strategy, scope, and objectives used to verify the quality of the Intercity Ride Sharing System.

Testing is designed to validate that the system behaves correctly under expected conditions and that it meets both functional and non-functional requirements.

Testing Objectives

-  The objectives of QA testing include:

- Ensuring that all core system features function as intended

- Detecting and reporting system defects

- Validating booking and payment workflows

- Ensuring seat availability and booking logic work correctly

- Verifying secure user authentication

- Confirming the system performs reliably during normal user activity

Test Scope

The following system modules are included within the QA testing scope.

##User Management

Testing verifies that users can successfully create and manage accounts.

This includes:

User registration

Login and logout functionality

Profile creation and editing

Role selection between Driver and Passenger

Testing also ensures that invalid input is handled correctly and that authentication mechanisms operate securely.

## Driver Features

Driver functionality is tested to ensure drivers can manage trips effectively.

This includes:

Posting new trips

Editing existing trips

Deleting trips

Viewing passenger booking requests

Accepting or rejecting passengers

Viewing trip history

These features are validated to ensure trip information is stored and updated correctly in the system.

## Passenger Features

Passenger features are tested to verify that passengers can easily find and book trips.

Testing includes:

Searching for available trips

Filtering trips by price, location, or time

Viewing trip details

##Booking seats

Viewing booking history

The goal is to ensure that passengers can locate and book rides without errors.

## Booking System

The booking system is tested to ensure seat management and booking logic work correctly.

Testing verifies that:

Seat availability is accurately tracked

Seat counts decrease after successful bookings

Users cannot book seats when none are available

Booking confirmations are generated correctly

These tests ensure the booking process remains consistent and prevents seat conflicts.

## Payment System

Payment functionality is tested to confirm that transactions are processed securely and correctly.

Testing verifies:

Successful payment processing

Recording of transaction details

Confirmation of successful payments

Handling of failed or incomplete transactions

These checks ensure financial transactions within the system remain accurate and secure.

 ## Rating and Review System

- The rating system allows users to provide feedback after completing trips.

Testing verifies that:

Passengers can rate drivers